<doc id="654998" wikidata="Q7913194" url="?curid=654998" title="Van Buren State Park (Michigan)">
<text>Van Buren State Park is a public recreation area on Lake Michigan south of South Haven, Michigan, United States. The state park, which is maintained and operated by the Michigan Department of Natural Resources, is located in the southwest corner of South Haven Township and the northwest corner of Covert Township, just north of the Palisades Nuclear Power Plant. The Van Buren County–owned North Point Conservation Area is located directly north of the park. The park has forested sand dunes, camping, and a swimming beach.

==History==
The park was established in 1966 following the state&#x27;s purchase of from the Harry LaBar Drake family in 1965. Two subsequent land purchases further expanded the park&#x27;s boundaries.

==Activities and amenities==
The park offers swimming, picnicking, playground, 220-site campground, and access to Van Buren Trail State Park.

